# React overlay
# Use with the base + typescript rules.

- React 18+. Function components only. No class components.
- Hooks at the top of the component body. No conditional hook calls.
- State that does not need to render belongs in `useRef`, not `useState`.
- Effects: only when external systems are involved. Prefer derived state.
- Memoize only with measured render cost. Do not wrap every callback in `useCallback`.
- Props are minimal. Pass primitives, not config objects, when possible.
- No `any` props. Define explicit prop types.
- Forms use uncontrolled inputs unless validation requires otherwise.
- Server Components: no event handlers, no `useState`. Client Components only when interactive.
- Tailwind class lists: keep them short; extract to a `cn()` helper or sub-component when over ~6 classes.
